    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Hey there! \ud83d\ude97 I'm parting ways with my trusty ride, and it's looking for a great new home. It\u2019s been well-loved and is in really solid shape\u2014perfect for someone who wants a reliable, stylish car without the brand-new price tag. It runs like a dream and has plenty of adventures left in it! Feel free to reach out if you want to take it for a spin!",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Up for sale is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six, renowned for its individual throttle bodies and linear power delivery up to an 8,000 RPM redline. This driver-focused example is mated to a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec M-Variable limited-slip differential. Mechanical highlights include a documented VANOS service and proactive rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring the structural rigidity of the chassis. The suspension geometry is maintained via refreshed control arms and Bilstein B6 dampers for precise turn-in. While showing minor aesthetic wear consistent with its mileage, the drivetrain remains tight with no parasitic loss or hesitation. A mechanically sound enthusiast's car ready for the canyons.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "Used car in good condition. Clean title. Full service history. Engine runs smooth. Interior is well-kept. Minor cosmetic blemishes on rear bumper.",
      "price": 28500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This vehicle represents a fantastic opportunity for a buyer who values mechanical integrity and a well-cared-for interior. The exterior presents beautifully in its original factory paint, maintaining a high gloss; however, in the interest of full transparency, there are a few minor stone chips on the hood and a small scuff on the lower rear bumper consistent with careful daily use. Inside, the cabin is a highlight\u2014the upholstery is firm and clean, the dashboard is free of any sun damage, and every button and switch operates with tactile precision. We have never smoked in this car, and the carpets have been protected by floor mats since day one. Under the hood, the engine is bone-dry and runs quietly. I have maintained a comprehensive service log, including a recent major interval service that covered fluid flushes and a new battery. The tires have approximately 70% tread remaining, and the brakes provide firm, confident stopping power. This is a solid, honest car that is ready for its next owner to drive home today.",
      "price": 34800.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_5_listing_5",
      "firm_id": "sybil_5",
      "description": "Presenting a distinguished example of automotive reliability and refined engineering. This vehicle has been meticulously maintained, reflecting a commitment to longevity and consistent performance. Both the exterior and interior remain in a commendable state, offering a sophisticated driving experience that exceeds standard expectations for its class. For the discerning buyer seeking a balance of luxury and proven dependability, this offering represents an exceptional acquisition.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
